# .dockerignore for the @offhours/api image (apps/api/Dockerfile).
#
# NOTE: the image is built from the REPO ROOT context (render.yaml sets
# dockerContext: .), so these patterns are matched against the monorepo root.
# Per docs/DEPLOYMENT.md / the deploy convention, this file INCLUDES src (the
# multi-stage build compiles TypeScript inside the image) and EXCLUDES
# *.tsbuildinfo. Shipping a stale .tsbuildinfo would make `nest build` think it
# is already up to date and emit NO JS, which boots into a crash. Excluding it
# forces a clean compile every build.

# --- Build outputs & incremental state (must NOT leak into the build context) ---
**/dist
**/build
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# --- Dependencies (reinstalled inside the image from the lockfile) ---
**/node_modules
**/.pnpm-store

# --- Secrets & local env (never bake into an image) ---
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# --- VCS / tooling / editor noise ---
.git
.github
.husky
.idea
.vscode
.impeccable
**/.DS_Store

# --- Sibling app & docs not needed to build the API ---
apps/web
docs

# --- Local-only infra ---
docker-compose.yml

# Keep source: apps/api/src and packages/shared/src are required by the build.
# (No ignore rule above touches **/src — it is intentionally included.)
